⚙️ Technologies Used
Terraform
AWS EC2
AWS VPC
AWS ALB (Application Load Balancer)
AWS Auto Scaling Group (ASG)
AWS RDS (MySQL)
AWS Security Groups
🔧 Modules Explanation
1. Infrastructure Module

Creates:

VPC
Public & Private Subnets
Internet Gateway
NAT Gateway
Route Tables
Security Groups

Outputs:

VPC ID
Subnet IDs
Security Group IDs
2. Frontend Module

Creates:

EC2 instances (Web servers)
Application Load Balancer (ALB)
Launch Template
Auto Scaling Group
3. Backend Module

Creates:

EC2 instances (App servers)
Internal Load Balancer
Launch Template
Auto Scaling Group
4. Database Module

Creates:

RDS MySQL instance
5. Bastion Module

Creates:

Bastion Host (for SSH access to private instances)
🔑 Key Concepts Used
✅ Modular Architecture

Each component is reusable and independent.

✅ Variables & Outputs
Inputs passed using variables.tf
Outputs shared between modules
✅ Dependency Management

Example:

module.vpc.vpc_id → used by ALB, EC2, RDS
⚠️ Common Errors & Fixes
❌ Key Pair Error
InvalidKeyPair.NotFound

✔ Fix:

Create key pair in AWS
Use correct name in Terraform
❌ Module Path Error
Unreadable module directory

✔ Fix:

Ensure correct folder names
Check spelling (loadbalancer vs loadblancer)
❌ RDS Free Tier Error
FreeTierRestrictionError

✔ Fix:

backup_retention_period = 0
❌ Idempotent Error
IdempotentParameterMismatch

✔ Fix:

terraform destroy
terraform apply
▶️ How to Run the Project
Step 1: Initialize Terraform
terraform init
Step 2: Plan Infrastructure
terraform plan
Step 3: Apply Configuration
terraform apply
Step 4: Destroy Resources
terraform destroy
🔐 Best Practices Followed
Use of modules for reusability
Separation of environments (dev)
Avoid hardcoding values (use variables)
Secure architecture with private subnets
Bastion host for SSH access
🎯 Interview Explanation (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 You can explain like this:

"I built a three-tier architecture using Terraform with modular design.
The infrastructure module creates the VPC, subnets, and networking.
The frontend and backend layers use ALB + Auto Scaling for scalability.
